Marathon Asset Management LP offered
a $75 million loan to finance the bankruptcy restructuring of
satellite communications company  TerreStar Networks Inc.  and
replace a loan from EchoStar Corp.  Marathon is ready to replace EchoStar as TerreStarâ€™s
bankruptcy lender,  Philip Anker , a lawyer for the hedge fund,
said at a hearing today in U.S. Bankruptcy Court in Manhattan.  TerreStar, based in Reston, Virginia, is seeking final
court approval of the $75 million loan from EchoStar. Marathon
and others oppose the EchoStar financing.  The case is In re TerreStar Networks Inc., 10-15446, U.S.
Bankruptcy Court, Southern District of New York (Manhattan).  To contact the reporter on this story:  David McLaughlin  in New
